SEQTOOLS
========

Description
-----------

Command line tool for manipulating DNA and protein sequence data in `.fasta` files.

Requirements

    * numpy
    * pandas
    * pyperclip
    * matplotlib


Installation
------------

To install type in terminal:

    $git clone git@github.com:polentozer/seqtools.git && cd seqtools && pip install .


Usage
-----

Translate DNA sequence to protein sequence using genetic code table provided in the default table and print the output

    $seqtools trans -i ">sample
    ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAGCTGTTTACAGGCGTTGTGCCCATCCTTGTGGAGCTTGACGG
    CGATGTCAACGGTCATAAGTTCTCCGTTCGAGGAGAAGGCGAGGGTGATGCCACCAACG
    GAAAGCTCACCCTTAAGTTCATCTGCACTACCGGTAAGCTGCCCGTGCCTTGGCCTACC
    CTGGTCACCACTCTCACCTATGGTGTGCAGTGCTTCGCCCGATACCCCGATCACATGAA
    GCAGCATGACTTTTTTAAGTCTGCCATGCCTGAAGGCTACGTCCAGGAGCGAACCATCT
    CTTTCAAGGATGATGGAACCTACAAGACCCGAGCTGAGGTCAAGTTTGAGGGTGATACT
    CTGGTCAACCGAATCGAGCTGAAGGGAATTGATTTTAAGGAGGATGGAAACATCCTCGG" -T

    $seqtools trans -i ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAG -T

    $seqtools trans -f sample.fasta -T

Translate DNA sequence to protein sequence using genetic code table provided in the default table and produce output file

    $seqtools trans -i ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAG -T -o

Optimize DNA sequence to a specified organism (default = Yarrowia lipolytica)

    $seqtools trans -i ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAG -O -on yali

Optimize DNA sequence to a specified organism (default = Yarrowia lipolytica) and change sequence to part type 3a

    $seqtools trans -i ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAG -O -oi 83333 -t 3a

Optimize DNA sequence to a specified organism (default = Yarrowia lipolytica) and draw graph for optimized and non-optimized sequence

    $seqtools trans -i ATGAGAAAGGGTGAGGAG -O -on ecoli -G

Harmonize DNA sequence to a source organism and draw graph for harmonized sequence

    $seqtools trans -f sample.fasta -H ecoli -on bsub -g

Harmonize DNA sequence to a source organism and produce output file and graphs

    $seqtools trans -f sample.fasta -H ecoli -on human -o -gh

Reverse translate protein sequence (codons chosen based on specified organism; default = Yarrowia lipolytica)

    $seqtools trans -i "MARKAPHID*" -on yeast

Generate 300 bp DNA sequence

    $seqtools gen 300

Generate 300 aa protein sequence

    $seqtools gen 300 -P
